TALENT NEEDED for Music Video!

**Date:** Saturday, December 13th

**Location**: Victorian mansion in Altadena, CA

**Rate**: $100/day (non-union): $100/day (non-union)

**Experience**: On-camera experience preferred, but not required

**Deadline**: Tuesday, November 11th at 11:59pm

**Additional**: Credit on distribution platforms and end-credits, BTS content, and permission to use in portfolios

Production title: Here Comes The Milkman

Union / Non-Union: Non-Union

Production Type: Independent

Project length: Short film

Project format: 4:3

Production Company: JMA FILMS 

Director: Justin Adams

Audition Location: Video Audition

Shooting Location:  Wrightsville PA

Email: Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com

Compensation: Unpaid. Food and IMDb credit only.

Synopsis: A boy won't finish his milk and so the babysitter tells him a story about a not so kind milkman

To be considered, you MUST send your CV/Resume to Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com. Do not use messenger. If you DO NOT reside in the DMV or York PA areas, we will not look at your submission unless you state you are willing to travel/lodge at your own expense. All actors will provide their own transportation.

The audition process:

1. Submit a resume or CV along with a head shot to Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com

2. Please state in the subject line the name of the character.

3. If selected, you will be given sides, instructions on how to submit, and a due date.

Any questions can be sent to the Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com email.

Hey LA actors,

I‚Äôm Maria, creative producer on a project happening Nov 15 ‚Äî and I had to share it here.

It‚Äôs an immersive audition experience that flips the whole thing on its head. We‚Äôre rethinking casting, performance, presence‚Ä¶ all of it.

Part workshop, part creative experiment. Honestly? I wish something like this existed when I was auditioning.

Early Bird ‚Äî $150 (until Nov 7)

Standard ‚Äî $190 (Nov 8‚Äì12)

Final ‚Äî $250 (Nov 13‚Äì15, if spots remain)

**10 spots only.**

Drop a comment or DM me - here's the link for sign ups 

‚Äî Maria Nova

items.text:
CASTING CALL FOR SHORT FILM (SPLENDOR) TO BE SHOT THIS WEEKEND, 8TH AND 9TH OF NOVEMBER | LONDON | RICHMOND PARK

TRAVEL AND EXPENSES COVERED

PAID

SYNOPSIS
An elderly dying blind poet and her violinist granddaughter she raised, go on a last trip to a spot where she was truly alive during her youth. Unknowingly, the journey will become an absolute metamorphosis for both.

Roles

**GRANDDAUGHTER AGE 19-25: A violinist and emerging poet who was adopted by her grandmother after the absence of her parents. She has a clinging bond with her grandmother and inwardly refuses to let go of her grandmother.**

**Grandmother AGE 55-80: A poet who has lost her sight and has stopped writing. She adopted her granddaughter, and the sound of her violin is the only thing that gives her joy. She wants to travel one last time to a nature spot where she felt most alive during her youth.**

(not obligatory but preferable with a fine art performance background)

CONTACT:

Instragram [@___reincarnated](https://www.instagram.com/___reincarnated/?hl=es)

**e-mail: K2554905@kingston.ac.uk**

items.text:
Hi There we're casting for two paid roles for a short film called Dead Funny. 1) Stanley - please only apply if you are a comedian. 2) Joshua - A corporate and dismissive boyfriend of black/british heritage.

If you're interested please keep reading below and apply by emailing: **deadfunnyshort@gmail.com**

**Story**
Minnie, a struggling comedian, moves into a new home with her boyfriend ‚Äî only to discover it‚Äôs haunted by Stanley, the ghost of a failed comic. At first hostile, Stanley becomes Minnie‚Äôs unlikely coach. Their chaotic and heartfelt friendship prepares her for one final shot at comedy ‚Äî and perhaps redemption for them both. But with a patronising boyfriend and a haunted past, Minnie must choose whether to stay small or take up space, on stage and in life.

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of text that says 'Casting call out for a paid opportunity for two actors for a short film called Dead Funny: -Joshua (playing age late 20s early 30s) Black British- Supportive in theory but patronising in practice. Joshua is corporate and arrogant. -Stanley (mid 40s to early 50s) White, cockney An east- east-end geezer. A brash, washed-up comic from another era with BIG personality -loud, offensive, outdated, but oddly charming. If either roles sound like you or know anyone interested please email deadfunnyshort@gmail.com for further details and audition slides.'

Hi everyone! We are casting for two theater performances of a new one act play to premiere in the West Village area! This is in conjunction with a wonderful presenting platform; roles are currently unpaid (possible deferred payment) and dates are blocked at various times within December 1st to December 6th.

We are looking for actors local to the NYC area; **black women aged 20-70**. Heavy consideration for those of Caribbean heritage. Roles as follows:

[ [OPAL](javascript:;) ]
Sixties, Jamaican woman who appears stush (regal). Grandmother. Classic clothing, well-tailored. Blunt, but sweet for a Jamaican.

[ [SAMMIE](javascript:;) ]
Late-thirties, hip Black woman. Aunt. Sarcastic queen.

[ [REESE](javascript:;) ]
Mid-forties, Black woman. Mother.

[ [COO](javascript:;) ]
LEAD. **40s and up to play 70s+ (can be aged)**, Jamaican woman. Well-tailored style, fully covered. Great-grandmother. Extremely blunt. 

Please submit here:

https://www.nycastings.com/job-notice/?Qn=111679&Qtitle=Bammy-an-Buxom-One-Act-Play-Casting-6-Roles-20-80

Or on Actor's Access here:

https://actorsaccess.com/projects/?view=breakdowns&breakdown=873983&region=32

Thanks so much!

MAIN $700/10

all rates are -20%af

Male actor, 25-40 years old, wanted.

You should be good-looking and well-built and not afraid of queer parts.

I'm an actor from Germany and from time to time I also make short films, which I present at international film festivals .

My films are arthouse films that may contain nudity and improvisation.

My upcoming short will be an online romance.

The actor should therefore record their part at home using their own smartphone.

Unfortunately, there's no payment, but it only takes 1-2 days. Sorry,  It's not possible to make money with a short film.
Filming will be in English.

I'm also looking for actors for potential future projects.

This is me: www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928

Please write to Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de

items.text:
Getting on set and working . Isn‚Äôt the what it‚Äôs all about? 

The Foundry Acting Studio our students aren‚Äôt only learning from a curriculum that‚Äôs been almost 7yrs in the making but has exceeded Spotlight approval by over 3x ‚Ä¶ also SAG recognised and soon to be many more. 

A curriculum that‚Äôs been sent to known actors , directors , casting and many other industry professionals throughout the world to approve before offering to any paying student. 

So‚Ä¶. Are you sick of not knowing where to sign up for classes . Sick of not knowing if it‚Äôs going to help . Sick of not knowing if it‚Äôs a scam. Sick of paying for classes and getting nowhere . 

Well not at The Foundry . Just check the progress and reviews for yourself .

sharedPost.text:
Real sets. Real productions. Real progress.

Here are Martin, Steve, and Sarah, three of our Foundry actors‚Ä¶‚Ä¶ behind the scenes of a major feature film.
They‚Äôre not pretending. They‚Äôre living it.

Steve trained with us for just three months and landed a supporting lead.
Martin came from a stunt background, no major dialogue experience and now he‚Äôs delivering key scenes as a supporting lead.
Sarah only started acting ten weeks ago‚Ä¶ and she‚Äôs already performing speaking roles on a professional feature film set.

This is what we do.
We don‚Äôt just talk about opportunity‚Ä¶.. we create it.
We train. We film. We deliver.

At The Foundry, our actors are working actors.
üé¨ The classroom is just the beginning, the set is where the learning continues.

Join us, and take your seat on set.
#TheFoundryActingStudio #HollywoodInTheNorth

Join us today . We are spotlight approved, SAG recognised and soon to be many more ‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.. 

Let‚Äôs get your journey started and get you on set .

Jeg kommer fra Danmark Radio, hvor vi her i Fakta- og Livsstilsafdelingen sidder og caster til et nyt TV-format. Vi leder efter par, som er i tvivl om, hvorvidt de skal have b√∏rn. 

I en verden med et stigende tempo, t√•rnh√∏je f√∏devarepriser, krig i Europa og klimaangst f√•r vi - som vi er blevet tudet √∏rerne fulde af - f√¶rre b√∏rn end nogensinde. Mere pr√¶cist 1,5 barn i stedet for 2,01 barn pr. Kvinde. For at nuancere problematikken har vi brug for nogle modige medvirkende, som t√∏r lukke os ind i deres tvivl. Er det jer?

I kan h√∏re mange flere detaljer om formatet, hvis I skriver til mig p√• tlf. 50906007 eller nedenfor i kommentarsporet. Jeg vil gl√¶de mig til at tale med jer allesammen :) 

De bedste hilsner

Clara Bruun, journalist, DR Aarhus

items.text:
Casting Brief

We are casting a drama scene that plays out in a VR training environment for security service industry personnel. This is a high drama realistic video, where you interact directly with the audience, looking into the lens, in the same way as in PeepShow.  Please read the casting breakdowns and only apply if you meet the requirements and are available on that shoot date. Please do not apply if you‚Äôre not. Full details on the application below.  We can't repsond to "interested". Please follow the details below. Thanks in advance.

Shoot Date: 19th November.  (locked no deviation on the date)

Shoot Times: Approx 8am - 7pm

Location:    Romford

Nearest Tube: Chadwell Heath (Elizabeth line)

Rick - Male 25-45 Any Ethnicity  - Security officer - calm and organised. Working security at high profile events. Someone who can be relied on. Professional look. Interacting with the lead

Steve  - Male 25-45 Any Ethnicity Security officer - lazy uninterested in taking things overly seriously. Does the bare minimum. Smart look overall. Interacting with the lead

Commander Alan - Male 35-50 Any Ethnicity - ex military type. Knows the seriousness of the job and what it takes to keep people safe. Interacting with the lead

Kelly - Female 24-35 Any Ethnicity - guest at the event, is involved in a high stress situation when during an attack she is separate from a loved one. Interacting with the lead

Stef - Female  25-45 Any Ethnicity - guest at the event, is involved in a high stress situation when during an attack she is separate from a loved one. Interacting with the lead

Ali - Waiter / waitress / host  Male / Female  25-45 Any Ethnicity - high end service industry professional working hard in the venue. Gets caught up in a high stress situation and tries to get past / around the lead

Danny - Photographer  Male / Female 25-45 a photographer with kit who is pushy about gaining access to certain areas, with or without rules being broken. Interacting with the lead

X - Male / Female 25-45 - this person is either a red herring or a criminal. Could they be doing something wrong, or just in the wrong place?  Interacting with the lead

The singer  - Male / Female 25-45 Any Ethnicity - performing on the main stage, solo gig to the audience, it‚Äôs your concert, your gig. Will be lip syncing to a couple of tracks while the experience plays out.

To apply please send an email with Subject Title ‚ÄúAudition T19 (and include the role‚Äù eg  Audition T19 Danny

Please send a brief email stating your experience and why you're suited to the role. 

Please include a recent headshot and full length.

Please include a youtube link to your showreel, if you don‚Äôt have a showreel a link to a brief monologue with an intro to who you are.

Please send submissions to info@ultrareality.co.uk

Paid: ¬£175

Use: private online in training app only. Not public.

Credits will be given

We‚Äôre looking for a special guest to join Maskara‚Äôs Hotline, a surreal 90s-style talk show that mixes absurd humor, performance art, and late-night energy.

The episode films Sunday, November 23 in Downtown LA. 

Who we‚Äôre looking for:

üé§ Someone semi-famous or with a public profile ‚Äî actor, musician, comedian, chef, tattoo artist, influencer, performer, or other creative figure with something to share.

üòÇ Must have a good sense of humor and be comfortable with playful, off-beat comedy.

üé¨ The tone is stylized, fast-paced, and visually bold ‚Äî think SNL meets Twin Peaks in pink latex.

‚ú® Full on-screen credit + IMDb listing

üéûÔ∏è High-quality footage for your portfolio or socials

‚Äî Lisa

Hi guys, I‚Äôm a student for the university of the arts London and I‚Äôm looking for a few actors to play in a short student film. 
We will be shooting for one day (10 hours including 1 hour break) on the 25th of November.  The main actress will have to be there for the whole day but the man and the older woman will have to be there for around 2 hours each. 

Food and transportation are covered by us.

We‚Äôre looking for **2‚Äì3 confident, camera-friendly individuals** for a **half-day lifestyle ad shoot** at a **private range near Greensboro, NC**.

You‚Äôll be on camera **wearing and using a holster**, demonstrating **product functionality**, and capturing **natural lifestyle b-roll** ‚Äî walking, drawing, adjusting, or simply moving through everyday concealed-carry scenarios.

This is **non-speaking work**, focused on short, authentic clips for **Facebook and Instagram ads**.

We need people who are:
* Comfortable being on camera and taking light direction
* Confident wearing holsters and being around firearms
* Available **Nov 8‚Äì9 **for a 4-hour shoot
* Local to **Greensboro,NC or surrounding areas**

This is a **paid opportunity, **paying out $20-40 / Hour, but with this being my first time booking this type of event please note I'm flexable and open to negotiation if needed** **‚Äî please include your **rate or day rate** when reaching out.

About us:
I‚Äôm **Austin**, co-owner and head of marketing at **Houdini Holsters** ‚Äî a veteran- and family-owned company designing holsters for undercover law enforcement and responsibly armed civilians. We‚Äôre expanding our ad library with new, high-quality b-roll for upcoming campaigns.

If interested,** text me directly at 336-482-8244** with your **name, photo or short clip, experience, and rate**.

Jianan Qu ‚Äî born in Shandong, China, lives and works in Vienna, Austria. He is the Director of the IDA ‚Äì Institute of Dance Arts at the Anton Bruckner University in Linz.
An interdisciplinary artist working with contemporary dance, performance, and installation. His works are characterized by minimalism, strong visual impact, and an exploration of presence and neutrality. He has collaborated with Theater St. Gallen, Festivalspielhaus St. P√∂lten, Liquid Loft, Editta Braun Company, x.IDA, and artists such as Charles Linehan, Liz King, Stephanie Cumming, Elio Gervasi, and Philipp Egli.
As a pedagogue, he has taught at numerous institutions and festivals across Europe and Asia. Recipient of the Best German Solo Dance Award 2007 and 1st Prize at the Szene Bunte W√§hne Choreography Competition 2006 in Vienna.

Open Call In Person Auditions Mon. & Tues. Nov 10 & 11 at 7pm for The 39 Steps by Patrick Barlow, Directed by Liz Bove. Performances: Jan. 9-18: Fri. & Sat. 8pm & Sundays 2pm + 2pm Matinee Sat. 1/17. More Details @ [https://www.facebook.com/share/17ZdspnYwH/](https://www.facebook.com/share/17ZdspnYwH/) Auditions @HeightsPlayers 26 Willow Place Brooklyn, NY 11201. (718) 237-2752. Please bring a headshot and resume, sides available on website. Please be sure to be available for in person call backs. NO pay.

CHARACTER BREAKDOWN:

**A familiarity with the Hitchcock film, The 39 Steps (1935), is highly recommended as the play is a direct spoof on the film. You may find this on ****[Youtube](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jfVtoPN3BVk)****.**
**Richard Hannay:** 30s-40s. A Hitchcock-esque suave, dashing, debonaire fellow. A physically adept comedian. Must be able to do a British accent. 

**Annabella Schmidt:** 20s-30s. An exotic and intriguing spy. Must be able to do a German accent. Actress will also play Margaret. 

**Pamela**: 20s-30s. The quintessential Hitchcock-esqe leading lady. She is bold, emotionally and intellectually intelligent. British accent required. 

**Margaret**: 20s-30s. The wife of a stern religious Scottish farmer. Scottish accent required. Actress will also play Annabella. 

**Clown #1 **& **Clown #2:** Any age, gender, race. Vivacious and debonair, both clowns expertly execute multiple male and female roles with skillful physical comedic skills.  English and Scottish accents a must.

Howdy Denver film community! We‚Äôre Wasteland of Wonder, a boutique film production company based here in Denver, CO that focuses on community building through creative collaboration. We‚Äôre seeking an actor for a music video and would love to engage with some new, local talent. Email us at wastelandofwonder@gmail.com for information about auditions!

TITLE: ‚ÄúDon‚Äôt Think‚Äù 

GENRE: Gothic industrial music video 

SYNOPSIS: ‚ÄúDon‚Äôt Think‚Äù explores themes of control and alienation both societally and personally with evocative and surreal imagery.  Our protagonist, Ezra, is an audience member at a surrealist concert- who slowly loses themself in the music. In a B plot we see manufacturers, men in a unique blend of industrial and medical garb, grooming and preparing Ezra for some kind of operation.  

CHARACTER: Ezra, (20s), feels alienated and unable to connect with others.  Ezra‚Äôs arc in the video is one of surrender and vulnerability, giving in to the pressures of everyone around them. 

This role is open casting for Men and Nonbinary actors of any race. Ideally the actor would be very skilled in physical work and have a dramatic background. 

PRODUCTION INFO

PRODUCTION COMPANY: Wasteland of Wonder (wastelandofwonder.com)

PRODUCTION TYPE: Music Video

CONTACT INFO: wastelandofwonder@gmail.com

COMPENSATION: The role will be compensated, rate TBD 

AUDITION INFORMATION: No audition, just send us a resume and reel :). Email us for further information. 

SHOOT SCHEDULE: Mid November 

FILMING LOCATION: Denver Metro & the Front Range

items.text:
CASTING CALL: Protesters Voiceover ‚Äì ‚ÄúDenied Care‚Äù Series

Project Title: Denied Care
Production Company: Superstar TV Entertainment, Inc.
Type: Voiceover (Non-Union / Indie Production)
Location: Remote Recording Accepted
Compensation: paid 
Recording Date: November 15th

Looking for 3 voiceovers

---

PROJECT OVERVIEW

Denied Care is a scripted drama following Ava Winters, a young woman denied life-saving treatment by a broken healthcare system. The story exposes the real human cost of bureaucratic neglect through emotional, defiant, and darkly comedic storytelling.

Short Film feature a pivotal protest montage ‚Äî where voices from across the nation rise in solidarity. This casting call is for those protester voices ‚Äî raw, real, and unapologetic.

---

ROLE: PROTESTER VOICEOVER (MULTIPLE TALENTS)

Gender: Any
Age Range: 18‚Äì65
Accent: Open ‚Äî diverse voices encouraged
Tone: Authentic, passionate, emotional, and real
Vocal Quality:

Gritty, tired, but determined

Feels like you‚Äôve lived it ‚Äî not ‚Äúperformed‚Äù it

Think real activists, not voice actors

Examples of Lines (for audition):

‚ÄúWe are not invisible!‚Äù

‚ÄúYou can‚Äôt deny care to the living!‚Äù

‚ÄúWe‚Äôre sick, not silent!‚Äù

‚ÄúEvery denial has a name!‚Äù

‚ÄúWe are the denied ‚Äî and we‚Äôre not backing down!‚Äù

(Actors may be asked to record crowd-style chants, overlapping dialogue, and emotional reactions.)

---

RECORDING NOTES

Please record clean audio (WAV or MP3) with minimal background noise.

Multiple takes with varying energy levels are encouraged.

Shouting, chanting, and overlapping crowd energy welcome.

Casting Call: Singer-Songwriter for Music Video (Unpaid)

Production Title: Christmas Music video 
Production Company: Superstar TV Entertainment Inc.
Type: Music Video
Location: Colorado (exact location TBD)
Filming Dates: late November early December 2025
Compensation: Unpaid (Copy, Credit, and Meals Provided)

---

About the Project

Superstar TV Entertainment Inc. is producing a heartfelt, cinematic music video featuring a singer-songwriter whose performance captures raw emotion and authenticity. This project is designed to highlight both the artist and visual storytelling ‚Äî similar in tone to Lewis Capaldi, Adele, or Noah Kahan.

The final video will be professionally shot and released across Superstar TV platforms, YouTube, and social media for maximum exposure.

---

Roles

üé§ Lead Artist / Singer-Songwriter (Principal Role)

Gender: Open to all

Age Range: 18‚Äì35

Vocal Style: Pop, acoustic, R&B, soul, or indie-folk preferred

Description: Emotionally expressive performer with on-camera presence. Must be comfortable lip-syncing to playback or performing live vocals. Guitar or piano ability is a plus.

Requirements: Must be reliable, punctual, and open to creative collaboration.

---

Supporting Roles (If applicable)

Love Interest: Ages 20‚Äì35, expressive and able to convey emotional connection.

Extras: Audience members, friends, or background talent for performance scenes.

---

Compensation

Unpaid (Copy, Credit, and Meals Provided)

You‚Äôll receive:

A professional-quality music video for your reel

IMDB credit under Superstar TV Entertainment Inc.

Networking opportunity for future paid productions

---

Submission Instructions

Please submit the following to tyler.schachtceo@outlook.com with the subject line:
Christmas Music Video ‚Äì [Your Name]‚Äù

Include:

Headshot or clear photo

Short performance clip or demo reel (YouTube or social media link accepted)

Short bio or resume

Contact information (email + phone number)

Personal Short Film Project

SEEKING 2 ACTRESSES FOR MAIN CAST

WHEN: Dec 20‚Äì23, 2025

PAID: CAD $150 / Day

Project Title:

The Thought Experiment ‚ÄúMETA MONTAGE‚Äù

Genre:

Meta-psychological Drama / Experimental Metafiction / Postmodern Romance

Logline:

When a screenwriter finds himself inside the very film he‚Äôs writing, reality and fiction intertwine ‚Äî forcing him, his characters, and even the audience to confront the question: Who is truly creating whom?

A visual and interactive interpretation of the Multiverse Theory.

Production Details:

Dates: December 20‚Äì23, 2025

Location: Vancouver, BC

Rate: CAD $150 / day

Type: Independent Short Film (non-union, paid)

Casting:

JUDY (20s‚Äì30s)

As Character, Actor, and Generative AI.

üéÑ Casting Call: Princess Isadora ‚Äì The North Pole Experience, Liverpool.üéÑ

We‚Äôre seeking to recast a female-identifying performer aged 18+ to play Princess Isadora, one of the North Pole‚Äôs most charming and magical residents.

The ideal performer will have strong, confident acting ability and a natural warmth on stage. A confident singer is a bonus but not essential. Princess Isadora is playful, kind, and full of festive spirit, someone who captures the wonder of Christmas for every guest she meets.

---

Requirements:

Availability: Must be available on all of the following dates:
22nd, 23rd, 29th, 30th November
6th, 7th, 13th, 14th, 20th, 21st, 22nd, 23rd, 24th December.

Any additional day of rehearsal will also be agreed with the successful applicant. 

Location: Liverpool, United Kingdom

Experience: Experience in entertainment or performance is a plus, but we also welcome enthusiastic newcomers with a passion for performing.

Personality: Must embody the spirit of Christmas and bring the character to life with warmth and confidence.

Pay:

Rehearsals paid hourly at the National Minimum Wage (NMW) for your age group.

Performance days paid at ¬£160 per day, depending on role and experience.

Lunch and refreshments provided on all performance days.

Cast members also receive complimentary tickets for our Friends & Family Day, plus staff discount in our on-site merchandise shop.

---

Application Details:
Please email casting@thenorthpoleexperience.co.uk with:

1. Full name and contact details (phone number, email address)

2. Role you‚Äôre interested in auditioning for

3. Relevant performance or entertainment experience (if applicable)

4. Confirmation of full availability for the listed dates

5. Recent headshot(s) and/or showreel

---

Help us bring the magic of Christmas to life at The North Pole Experience ‚Äî we can‚Äôt wait to make magic with you! ‚ú®

**SUCHE ERFAHRENE THEATERBEOBACHTERIN F√úR OUTFIT-BERATUNG - MONOLOG √úBER GENDER FLUIDITY**

Ich bin ein professioneller Schauspieler mit internationalem Hintergrund und arbeite an einem **Monolog √ºber Geschlechtsfluidit√§t und Identit√§t**.

**ICH SUCHE:** Eine Theater-Beraterin/Beobachterin mit: ‚ú® Tiefem Verst√§ndnis zeitgen√∂ssischer Theatersprache ‚ú® Raffiniertem √§sthetischem Geschmack und visueller Sensibilit√§t ‚ú® F√§higkeit, fundierte Meinungen auf Basis von Branchenerfahrung zu √§u√üern ‚ú® Verst√§ndnis f√ºr Gender-Fluidity-Themen und B√ºhnenrepr√§sentation ‚ú® Kompetenz im Vorschlagen fotografischer Posen und K√∂rperdynamik

**ARBEITSWEISE:**
* Prim√§r: Outfit-Bewertung durch **Online-Fotoeinsendung**
* Bei geografischer N√§he: M√∂glichkeit **pers√∂nlicher** Beratung

**DAS PROJEKT:** Ein Monolog, der Geschlechtsidentit√§t, Fluidit√§t und Performativit√§t erforscht. Ich brauche einen Expertenblick, um eine koh√§rente visuelle Dramaturgie durch Outfits aufzubauen.

**IDEALES PROFIL:**
* Theaterkritiker*in, Dramaturg*in, Regisseur*in oder Performance-Forscher*in
* Kenntnisse der Gender Studies im B√ºhnenkontext
* Erfahrung im zeitgen√∂ssischen und/oder experimentellen Theater
* Sensibilit√§t f√ºr Charakterkonstruktion durch Kost√ºm

üìß [matteo@matteolaporta.eu](mailto:matteo@matteolaporta.eu)

Casting for *"Love in an STD Clinic,"* a short film following two women **Nora and Kai**, strangers who meet and fall in love while waiting in an STD clinic. Their connection is meaningful but fleeting, as Nora is leaving for university at the end of the year ‚Äî forcing them to face the reality of their brief romance.

üìÖ **Shooting Date:** November 20, 2025
üìç **Location:** London
üí∏ **Unpaid**, but **food and transportation are covered**

We are currently casting for **Kai**:
* **Kai:** Woman in mid 20s to early 30s, person of any ethnicity. A **charming, masc lesbian** ‚Äî confident, emotionally open, and able to bring warmth and humour to awkward situations.

 üé• **Audition Details:**

Auditions will be **via self-tape**. If you‚Äôre interested, please **DM me** or comment below ‚Äî I‚Äôll send you the script and details for the self-tape once you confirm your interest.

Produced by **Farah Hammad**, UAL Film Practice student.

Hej alle sammen!

Jeg kommer fra Danmark Radio, hvor vi her i Fakta- og Livsstilsafdelingen sidder og caster til et nyt TV-format. Vi leder efter par, som er i tvivl om, hvorvidt de skal have b√∏rn. 

I en verden med et stigende tempo, t√•rnh√∏je f√∏devarepriser, krig i Europa og klimaangst f√•r vi - som vi er blevet tudet √∏rerne fulde af - f√¶rre b√∏rn end nogensinde. Mere pr√¶cist 1,5 barn i stedet for 2,01 barn pr. Kvinde. For at nuancere problematikken har vi brug for nogle modige medvirkende, som t√∏r lukke os ind i deres tvivl. Er det jer?

I kan h√∏re mange flere detaljer om formatet, hvis I skriver til mig p√• tlf. 50906007 eller nedenfor i kommentarsporet. Jeg vil gl√¶de mig til at tale med jer allesammen :) 

De bedste hilsner

Clara Bruun, journalist, DR Aarhus

items.text:
CASTING CALL FOR SHORT FILM (SPLENDOR) TO BE SHOT THIS WEEKEND, 8TH AND 9TH OF NOVEMBER | LONDON | RICHMOND PARK

TRAVEL AND EXPENSES COVERED

PAID

SYNOPSIS
An elderly dying blind poet and her violinist granddaughter she raised, go on a last trip to a spot where she was truly alive during her youth. Unknowingly, the journey will become an absolute metamorphosis for both.

Roles

**GRANDDAUGHTER AGE 19-25: A violinist and emerging poet who was adopted by her grandmother after the absence of her parents. She has a clinging bond with her grandmother and inwardly refuses to let go of her grandmother.**

**Grandmother AGE 55-80: A poet who has lost her sight and has stopped writing. She adopted her granddaughter, and the sound of her violin is the only thing that gives her joy. She wants to travel one last time to a nature spot where she felt most alive during her youth.**

(not obligatory but preferable with a fine art performance background)

CONTACT:

Instragram [@___reincarnated](https://www.instagram.com/___reincarnated/?hl=es)

**e-mail: K2554905@kingston.ac.uk**

items.text:
# **MODEL CALL - PROJECT LAUNDRY (PAID / NON-UNION)**

Union Status: Non-Union

Shoot Date: November 12, 2025

Location: Vancouver - West Side (must have own transportation)

Rate: $300 for 6 hours + crafty provided

 **PROJECT OVERVIEW**

We are casting for a social campaign promoting a local laundry service. We are looking for authentic, real-world talent who reflect the diversity and warmth of everyday Canadians.

## **TALENT REQUIREMENTS**

‚Ä¢ Mix of male and female talent

‚Ä¢ Represent everyday Canadians who work as independent contractors from home

‚Ä¢ Inclusive of all ethnicities, backgrounds, and body types

‚Ä¢ Professional appearance yet approachable and relatable

‚Ä¢ Comfortable participating in both photography and videography

‚Ä¢ No modelling or acting experience required, but comfortable in front of camera

## **HOW TO SUBMIT**

Send your headshot + resume or Instagram handle to: projectlaundrycasting@gmail.com

About Us
The Uzual Suspects Casting Agency is a proudly South African-based casting and extras coordination agency, operating since 2018. We work behind the scenes to help bring incredible stories to life ‚Äî connecting talent with opportunity across film, television, and digital productions.
Our Talent
With a growing database of over 1,000 talented actors, actresses, artists, and models, we take pride in representing individuals who continue to make us proud on some of the biggest local and international stages. Our artists have been featured in productions on Netflix, DStv, BET, and many more renowned platforms.
What We Do

üé¨ **CASTING CALL ‚Äì ‚ÄúVANILLA SHAKE‚Äù (Short Film)** üé¨
**Los Angeles | Shooting Dec 2025 | Non-Union | Unpaid (copy, credit, meals, footage)**

Hey filmmakers & actors ‚Äî I‚Äôm casting for my indie short ***Vanilla Shake***, a gritty **neo-noir crime drama** with strong performances and 90s cinematic style (*think* *Drive* √ó *Breaking Bad* √ó *Reservoir Dogs*).

**üìç Location:** Los Angeles
**üìÖ Shoot:** 3 days in December (TBD)
**üé• Tone:** Dark, stylish, character-driven

üîπ MICKEY

Male, 40-60
A bruised soul with street smarts and scars. Tough, conflicted, oddly loyal.
*References:* Benicio Del Toro (*Sicario*), Harvey Keitel (*Bad Lieutenant*).

üîπ BOSSMAN

Male, 50‚Äì60
A calm, philosophical predator. Power through silence.
*References:* Ray Liotta (*Goodfellas*), Ian McShane (*Deadwood*).

**About the Film:**
*Vanilla Shake* dives into masculinity, moral decay, and redemption through a doomed friendship. Minimalist dialogue. Real emotion. Heavy atmosphere.

üì© **TO SUBMIT:**
Send a quick intro (or self-tape), headshot, and reel (if available) to:

üëâ **jcastingservices@gmail.com**
Include the role + your December availability.

Let‚Äôs make something raw, cinematic, and unforgettable.
‚Äì **Jason R. Farabaugh | Writer / Director**

topComments.text:
Unless it's a student production ALWAYS pay your cast and crew. Start a crowdfunding campaign, apply for grants, take out a personal bank loan, hold bake sales and car washes, meet with local/regional businesses for product placement.

Even Spike Lee, before he was "Spike Lee" got financing for his first film "She's Gotta Have It" when no one even knew who Spike Lee was..But STOP this practice of expecting Actors and Crew to work for free on your films.

What about liability insurance to cover the cast and crew on set? A film set is a place where a lot of incidents could happen. What if they get hurt on set? How are you going to compensate them for their medical expenses and lost work time? How are you going to cover equipment damaged or lost to such a situation? What if the property (house, offices, vase, etc. ) gets damaged, how are you going to cover those expenses?

What about a completion bond to insure the film is finished or pay the people for their time if it's not? Do you have that? 

My point is you have to start treating your business as a BUSINESS and stop expecting cast and crew to work for free. Filmmaking isn't just shooting footage on set and cutting it together in post. Part of filmmaking is finding the funding to make a film. And if you don't want to do that legwork then you don't really want to be in the film industry.

Male actor, 25-40 years old, wanted.

You should be good-looking and well-built and not afraid of queer parts.

I'm an actor from Germany and from time to time I also make short films, which I present at international film festivals .

My films are arthouse films that may contain nudity and improvisation.

My upcoming short will be an online romance.

The actor should therefore record their part at home using their own smartphone.

Unfortunately, there's no payment, but it only takes 1-2 days. Sorry,  It's not possible to make money with a short film.
Filming will be in English.

I'm also looking for actors for potential future projects.

This is me: www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928

Please write to Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de
